            </sparkle:deltas>
            <description><![CDATA[
            					<h2>New Features</h2>
            					<ul>
            						<li>The eyes of the daruma in the Dock tile and app icons displayed in the app are now filled in based on in-progress and completed goals. Please note that Daruma’s Dock Tile extension must be enabled in System Settings for this feature to work when the app is not running.</li>
            					</ul>
                            <h2>Fixes and Improvements</h2>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Fixes several issues with the app’s database</li>
                                <li>Fixes minor issues with the interface</li>
                                <li>Includes a hidden feature coming in a future release. Can you unlock it? (It is difficult to find and there is no prize!)</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h2>Known Issues</h2>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Scrolling the goal list may not work as intended and exhibit some “stuttering.” We are working on a solution and apologize for any inconvenience.</li>
                                <li>When burning completed goals, the “burning” animation may not appear on macOS 26 Tahoe. We are investigating the issue and apologize for the absence of this fun feature.</li>
                            </ul>
							]]></description>
